# Multiplayer Shooting Game - Server Configuration Example
# =========================================================
# This file contains server configuration only.
# Client will prompt user to enter server address when starting.

# SERVER CONFIGURATION
# Bind address: 0.0.0.0 (all interfaces), localhost (local only), or specific IP (192.168.1.100)
SERVER_HOST=0.0.0.0

# Server port - must be between 1024 and 65535
SERVER_PORT=5555

# ================================================
# CONFIGURATION EXAMPLES
# ================================================

# EXAMPLE 1: Local testing (single computer, multiple terminals)
# SERVER_HOST=0.0.0.0
# SERVER_PORT=5555
# 
# Client will prompt:
#   Enter server address: localhost
#   Enter server port: 5555

# EXAMPLE 2: Home network play (multiple computers)
# SERVER_HOST=192.168.1.100          (change to your server IP)
# SERVER_PORT=5555
#
# Client will prompt:
#   Enter server address: 192.168.1.100
#   Enter server port: 5555

# EXAMPLE 3: Custom port for multiple game instances
# SERVER_HOST=0.0.0.0
# SERVER_PORT=9999                   (different port for Game #2)
#
# Client will prompt:
#   Enter server address: localhost
#   Enter server port: 9999

# EXAMPLE 4: Localhost only (no network access)
# SERVER_HOST=127.0.0.1
# SERVER_PORT=5555
#
# Client will prompt:
#   Enter server address: 127.0.0.1
#   Enter server port: 5555

# ================================================
# COMMON NETWORK ADDRESSES
# ================================================

# 0.0.0.0          - Listen on all network interfaces (server only)
# 127.0.0.1        - Localhost (local computer only)
# localhost        - Localhost by hostname
# 192.168.x.x      - Private IP address (home/local network)
# 10.x.x.x         - Private IP address (home/local network)
# 172.16-31.x.x    - Private IP address (home/local network)

# ================================================
# PORT INFORMATION
# ================================================

# Valid port range: 1024 - 65535
# Common ports:
#   5555 - Default game port
#   8080 - HTTP
#   3306 - MySQL
#   5432 - PostgreSQL
# 
# If port 5555 is in use, try: 9999, 7777, 6666, 8888, etc.

# ================================================
# FINDING YOUR IP ADDRESS
# ================================================

# Linux/Mac:
#   hostname -I
#   ifconfig | grep "inet " | grep -v 127.0.0.1

# Windows:
#   ipconfig
#   Look for "IPv4 Address" under your network adapter

# ================================================
# FIREWALL CONFIGURATION
# ================================================

# For network play to work, firewall must allow:
# 
# Windows:
#   1. Windows Firewall > Allow an app through firewall
#   2. Click "Change settings"
#   3. Find Java in the list and allow it
#   4. If not listed, browse to your Java executable and add it
#
# Linux (UFW):
#   sudo ufw allow 5555
#
# Mac:
#   System Preferences > Security & Privacy > Firewall
#   May need to allow Java or add an exception

# ================================================
# WORKFLOW
# ================================================

# 1. Edit .env with your server configuration
# 2. Run server: java -cp ... com.kaiounet.GameServerApp
# 3. Run client: java -cp ... com.kaiounet.GameClientApp
# 4. Client will prompt you for server address and port
# 5. Client connects to server
# 6. Game starts!

